OL,3,CEmployers warned to protect workers
OL,4,Cfrom sexual harassment ahead of new law
OL,6,FAlesha De-Freitas, head of policy at
OL,7,Fthe Fawcett Society, said: "For too
OL,8,Flong perpetrators have been able to
OL,9,Fhide because of workplace cultures
OL,10,Fthat enable harassment and collude in
OL,11,Fcover-ups. This is about to change.
OL,13,F"From the end of October employers
OL,14,Fwill be required to prevent sexual
OL,15,Fharassment from happening in the first
OL,16,Fplace.
